    "updated_at": "2014-08-21T04:55:28Z",
    "body": "I think what would make sense here is to move the documentation for all of the `std` reexported crates (`core`, `alloc`, etc) out of the \"main\" API docs into a separate set. That way the \"normal\" use case of just using `std` will be more straightforward, as will the other use case of running with `#[no_std]`, since both groups will only be searching the docs that apply to them.\n",
